Female
. Similar to female except for: apical margin of sternite 8 with short setae; tergite 10 with posterior margin weakly pigmented, with short fringes and four setae on each side at apex (
Fig. 93
); bursa copulatrix elongated (
Fig. 92
); ovipositor consisting of a pair of weakly pigmented hemisternites and a pair of more apical coxites, and with many long setae on apex; spermatheca with globose capsule (
Fig. 94
).
